COPY public.series_trope (series_name, trope_name, trope_usage) FROM stdin;
Abnormal Summit	Fun with Foreign Languages	Frequently. In one episode Alberto teaches the other cast members a song. Yuan can't be compelled to sing along, because the refrain sounds too similar to a Chinese swear word.
Abnormal Summit	Model United Nations	Kind of...rather than making resolutions, they decide whether or not the panelist was abnormal. And there's a lot more humor in the process.
Abnormal Summit	Running Gag	Especially in the early episodes, this was drilled a lot. One could make a Drinking Game out of this.
Abnormal Summit	Screw the War, We're Partying	How Lebanon is viewed during the Middle East conflicts. Visiting intern Samer Samhoun confirms this.
ABC World News Tonight	HR Baukhage	ekdays
ABC World News Tonight	Ted Koppel	ekends
ABC World News Tonight	Human-Interest Story	During David Muir's run, he has done stories about people going through difficult times but managing to pull through, either because of illnesses like cancer or people who have died during the COVID-19 pandemic.
ABC World News Tonight	Precision F-Strike	On one outtake from 1979, Max was in Chicago, and a plane crash had just happened there. Unfortunately for him, Frank Reynolds always led off from Washington, and had that plane crash as the lead item. Max blew up in this outtake (caught on a satellite feed), with some major foul language (quote has most of the foul language redacted in blanks)...Max Robinson: Then I dare you to do that ______! How the hell do you let that man in Washington update my _______ story! There's no ______ excuse for it, _______ it—don't tell me there's one for it! I'm working my _____ off—now let's get something done out of you!
