Abbott Elementary	Hard Truth Aesop	While the show has a theme of making do even in sub-optimal situations, it is also very unsubtle about telling the viewer that, in America, public schools are in dire situations and require more funding to take care of the children, especially in underprivileged neighborhoods.
Abbott Elementary	Hates Small Talk	In "Mom", we learn that Gregory is bad at small talk and doesn't see the point of it. Jacob and Melissa point out that it's actually a very useful social skill, especially for someone who wants to be in an administrative position such as principal. He manages to find something in common with Shanae at the end of the episode: they're both Orioles fans.
Abbott Elementary	Horrible at Horticulture	Jacob and Barbara set up a vegetable garden in Season 1. They are hopeless at it, so Gregory, whose father runs a Family Business in landscaping (a fact that he's hidden from them due to his own dislike of gardening), sneaks in and tends to it so the plants won't die. This gets revealed to them in Season 2 when Gregory's father Martin comes for a visit.
Abbott Elementary	Hypocritical Humor	In "Mom", Ava tells Janine not to make fun of herself, because then it's less fun for Ava when she does it.
