Abbott Elementary	Mama Bear	Vanetta may be a neglectful freeloader, but she squares up when Ava insults Janine. In the same episode, Barbara steps in when she becomes worried that Vanetta is going to guilt-trip Janine into giving up her vacation money so Vanetta can pay her phone bill, defending Janine and even offering to give Vanetta the money herself.
Abbott Elementary	Mocking Music	When Ava finds out that the Superintendent married the woman he had an affair with and thus her blackmail on him is useless and she needs to shape up and be an actual principal or be fired, she plays Mary J. Blige 's "I'm Goin' Down".
Abbott Elementary	Mockumentary	The teachers are indeed being followed around by a documentary crew documenting the struggles of teachers in the public school system. This gets weaponized against them in "Attack Ad", when the teachers find out that Legendary Charters was able to get footage for their negative ad by sending in a fake camera crew.
Ace Lightning	Downer Ending	Several episodes, including April Fools and Unidentified Flying Superhero.
Abbott Elementary	Newscaster Cameo	One from Philly's legendary news anchor Jim Gardner (not coincidentally, the anchor at the ABC station in town, WPVI-TV). Quinta Brunson later made an appearance during WPVI's Thanksgiving Day Parade coverage (not long before Gardner officially retired in December of 2022), and both geeked out over each other.
Abbott Elementary	Not So Above It All	Despite his best efforts, Gregory eventually gets sucked into caring about his students, his job, and Abbott Elementary.
Abbott Elementary	Not What It Looks Like	Janine and Gregory's first meeting in the pilot. Janine walks into one of the bathrooms with a sick student in tow and sees a strange man emerging from a stall with a pair of child's pants in his hand. She naturally freaks out until Gregory manages to explain himself (one of his students had to go to the bathroom and wet his pants).Janine: Random man! Child pants! Security!
