A Bit Of Fry And Laurie	Gargle Blaster	In seasons 3 and 4, the show would end with a cocktail being selected and mixed. These started with relatively reasonable suggestions, such as the Whiskey Thunder, involving whiskey, angostura bitters, lemon juice, a pint of oh-so-fresh dairy cream, two olives, and a peanut.note This would in fact be pretty disgusting: the whisky would be heavily diluted by all that cream, which in turn would be curdled by the lemon juice, so you'd end up with a salty, bitter, mildly alcoholic mix of curds and whey. Hugh grimaces visibly when he takes a sip. They then became increasingly absurd, culminating at the end of season 4 with the Modern Britain, which takes Stephen over a minute and a half to describe while the Union Jack is lowered behind him.
A Bit Of Fry And Laurie	The Ghost	Mr. Dalliard, and Valerie from the Tony & Control sketches. Marjorie is almost The Ghost, but does make one appearance.
