A For Andromeda	Hollywood Silencer	The bowler-hatted Intel assassin uses a .25 Beretta with a miniscule silencer that makes so little sound it can be covered by a camera flash.
A For Andromeda	Improperly Placed Firearms	The British soldiers who recapture Fleming carry World War II Lee Enfield bolt-action rifles and a German MP40 submachine gun (the soldiers in the first serial are correctly armed with L1A1 self-loading rifles).
A For Andromeda	Just Friends	Fleming on his relationship with Andromeda (though he kisses her at the end)."We are what is popularly known as just friends."
A For Andromeda	Qurac	Azaran, a newly-independent Middle Eastern country which hopes to use the computer to resolve its agricultural problems.
A For Andromeda	Reluctant Mad Scientist	Scientists are lured to Azaran by Intel under various pretexts, whereupon they discover You Can Never Leave.
A For Andromeda	Shell-Shocked Veteran	The hermit, implied by his possession of a German MP40 submachine gun and his desire to live away from human contact.
A For Andromeda	Trolling Translator	When Kaufman announces that Intel has effectively taken over Azaran, the translator shows his disapproval by talking loudly over him. Also this scene:Kaufman: "The army and all other branches will report directly to the President. The present parliament will not be called back into session. Help will continue to be provided by..."(Translator gives long stream of Arabic)Kaufman: "...a new international technological and trading consortium..."Translator: "Intel."(Kaufman glares at translator)
