After Midnight	Anti-Climax	On February 26, 2024, they played a game with the unabashedly long title How Long Until They Put A Full Slice Of American Cheese In It, where the object is to guess just that for a TikTok recipe video. Panelists have to wager their points on their guess, so Marc Maron makes a big show of how hard a struggle it is to decide, before he finally settles on 11 seconds (while Zainab Johnson picks 3, and Brendan Hunt picks 1). The video plays, and the cheese lands on the prepared food at 12 seconds, giving Marc the points by a landslide. And how many points did he wager for this epic victory?Marc: ...four. Taylor: [incredulous] Four points?? Marc: Yeah. [Marc gets four points as Brendan starts snickering, while Zainab and Taylor are dying laughing]
After Midnight	Anti-Humor	Frequently used by Reggie Watts whenever he shows up, like the Cloud Cuckoolander he is. Also, Zach Cherry appeared once and invoked this a couple times, just to nerd out about science instead of giving any proper answer. Even Pete Holmes was bewildered by Zach.
After Midnight	Attention Deficit... Ooh, Shiny!	Introducing a game where contestants have to pay attention to details in a short video, Taylor invokes this:Taylor: If there's one thing we can all agree on, it's... wait, what was I saying? ...oh yeah, attention spans! [audience groan-laughs] You thought I [bleep]ed up, but it was in the prompter!
After Midnight	Audience Participation	Much like the original, viewers are encouraged to post their own responses for the Hashtag Wars, with the producers' favorite shown on the next episode.
After Midnight	Badass Boast	aylor: Megan Gailey. In a word, give us your five-year plan. Megan Gailey: [dramatically turns to face the camera] EGOT.
After Midnight	Big "NO!"	One round of Hashtag Wars has Caitlin Reilly getting perpetually beaten to the buzzer by Gillian Jacobs and Pete Holmes, and she slowly goes nuts until the round ends, with Caitlin only getting in a measly two responses. The ending buzzer causes her to scream "NOOOOOOOOOO!!!" at the top of her lungs... and then reach over to Taylor's podium to give herself more points... only for them to go to Pete instead.
After Midnight	Bitch in Sheep's Clothing	Caitlin Reilly adopts this persona whenever she appears. Very nice and complementary to Taylor, then proceeding to be a Competition Freak and Drama Queen.
After Midnight	Biting-the-Hand Humor	
After Midnight	Black Comedy	The second episode has a game about figuring out what movie a dodgy review is about, and the first one just says "this happened to my buddy Eric".Sophie Buddle: The Passion of the Christ.Paul F. Tompkins: Blackfish.Carl Tart: May December.
After Midnight	Black Comedy Burst	
After Midnight	Blunt "No"	Esther Povitsky competed while 8 months pregnant, so Taylor brings this up in the Talk Show Portion:Taylor: Esther, you are 8 months pregnant. [audience cheers] I know! And therefore a hero! Do you like being pregnant? Esther: Ummm... no. Let's just say that if anyone in this room could perform an illegal c-section, I would let them.
After Midnight	Break the Haughty	Catherine Cohen comes into her episode very cocky (playfully of course), at one point buzzing in and calling on herself before Taylor can. She carries this energy right up until she's eliminated, which prompts a Jaw Drop from her. And just to rub it in, she's swiftly whisked off stage by a Vaudeville Hook.
After Midnight	Breaking News Interruption	invoked The September 30, 2024 episode contains one of these...which turns out to just be a setup to a game claiming Moo Deng (a baby pygmy hippo) was arrested for biting its zookeeper.
After Midnight	Brick Joke	Nish Kumar gets eliminated in one episode and is tasked to tell the audience something he's never told anyone. So Nish replies, cryptically, that he's stolen three computers from the Paramount lot. When he comes back on stage to congratulate the winner at the end credits, somehow he's holding three laptops.
After Midnight	Butt-Monkey	
After Midnight	Cast Full of Gay	This show leans into queer comedians noticeably more than its predecessor did. It's not uncommon for entire panels to be out and proud, and lest we forget, Taylor is proudly bisexual herself.
After Midnight	Celebrity Impersonator	
After Midnight	Chekhov's Gag	Bit of a subtle one — on February 5, 2024, Taylor asked Bianca Del Rio "what you would change about me" and Bianca, being Bianca, misdirected for a good while before a very curt "change your hair." The very next night, viewers noticed that Taylor did, in fact, wear her hair down for the first time in a while. (After all, when a Drag Queen gives you fashion advice, you take it.)
After Midnight	Cloud Cuckoolander	
After Midnight	Comically Missing the Point	During the Talk Show Portion on February 7, 2024:Taylor: London, what's your favorite flavor? London Hughes: I would have to say... Flav. [London is awarded points by Taylor] Taylor: [laughing] I'm not even supposed to give points on this, but I did!
After Midnight	Freeze-Frame Bonus	The prize for September 23, 2024 is a to-do list from "someone very important". Pausing and reading it before we get to Taylor's jokes reveals that it's just chock full of jokes about Zendaya.
After Midnight	From Bad to Worse	It isn't bad enough that Fortune Feimster gets eliminated and has to give the usual losing speech; no, Taylor then finds a baby picture of her in a bonnet and puts it on the screen for all to see.
Aikatsu Planet	Maybe Magic, Maybe Mundane	The mechanics behind the Aikatsu Planet! world aren't really explained.
After Midnight	Competition Freak	It's a fake game show, as Taylor loves to remind us, but occasionally a panelist proves to be a bit competitive and leans toward Serious Business. Catherine Cohen and Caitlin Reilly (the latter of whom went so far as to suck up to Taylor and call her "mommy") are notable examples, and Marcella Arguello was this on her first appearance (until Large Ham Marcella decided it was more fun to do an elimination). Matt Rogers was a particularly humorous example.Taylor: [after Hashtag Wars] My favorite part of that whole thing was when Matt- when James buzzed in and Matt was just like "NO!!!!!" Matt Rogers: I'm competitive!! Taylor: [laughing] That was so raw and real and genuine!
After Midnight	Coordinated Clothes	On the June 6, 2024 edition, Kelsey Cook, Brian Simpson and Blair Socci all wore suits identical to Taylor's just for a gag. Taylor, of course, is delighted.
After Midnight	Courtroom Episode	A game is played on the June 18, 2024 edition called Innocent Or Guilty Pleasure, where the cast have to take turns defending one of their guilty pleasures, while the others rotate as prosecutor and judge, in terrible Party City wigs and clip-on ties. It allows for some beautifully Large Ham speeches, especially given that the cast in question is Patton Oswalt, Terry Crews and Joe Manganiello. The game returned the next season, this time with the cast being Dylan Adler, Atsuko Okatsuka, and Reggie Watts.
After Midnight	Cuteness Overload	October 23, 2024 — Taylor attempts to introduce a game involving telling your secrets to a small puppy in an armchair. "Attempts" being the operative word here, since Taylor did not see the tiny little pupper beforehand, and Taylor has to have a crying meltdown at how perfect this sweet little angel is before she can introduce the game properly.
After Midnight	Creepy Doll	Throughout multiple shows, Taylor tries to offer a "haunted" doll her brother gave her as the prize. Each time though, the doll was given back to her despite her pleas. Eventually she manages to give the doll away for real to Marcella Arguello... only for a fan to send Taylor an exact replica of said doll, leading to a later episode where Taylor offers that as a prize while looking absolutely livid. Marcella would proceed to Troll Taylor by bringing the doll back with her on two subsequent appearances, including the Grand Finale!
After Midnight	Cringe Comedy	Max Greenfield. Full stop. He squeezes out a few jokes during his appearance, but most people remember him for being very awkward and out-of-place on this show. They play Kill The Vibe during this episode, where panelists have to make unnecessarily dark/harsh comments on wholesome, heartwarming videos. Max refuses to go that dark and just keeps answering with the most innocuous comments he can think of... which kills the vibe in the studio. Fellow panelist James Davis loves it.
After Midnight	Crowd Chant	
After Midnight	Dark Secret	The point of the game What's Their Secret? Panelists get a stock photo of someone looking shifty-eyed, and have to buzz in with what their secret could be.[image of a man and a woman holding hands, directly behind the back of another girl] Taylor: What's their secret? [chime] Jeff. Jeff Hiller: The middle girl doesn't have a face! [Taylor laughs herself silly] It's probably true!
After Midnight	Darkhorse Victory	Still happens sometimes. Being a big name, or even having a particularly dominant performance during the show, does not guarantee a win.
After Midnight	Death Glare	Taylor developed one on March 6, 2024, when she slowly realized Adam Pally was going to milk his Overly Long Gag for the entire show.
After Midnight	Didn't Think This Through	
After Midnight	Disapproving Look	
After Midnight	Dramatic Gasp	Taylor once introduces a prompt about drama in the needlepoint community (of all places) by gratuitously invoking this.Taylor: Drama is everywhere. Even here. Watch. [cut to camera 2, where an orchestral sting plays while Taylor makes a Dramatic Gasp at the camera] Taylor: [to the audience] Thank you. That'll make more sense later when you watch it at home.
After Midnight	Dude, Not Funny!	During a round of Dumb Dog, Smart Dog, Andy Richter is given a picture of a corgi holding a big branch in its mouth. Andy immediately decides that it's a dumb dog, because corgis are "too low to the ground to be smart." The two significantly shorter panelists next to him, Aparna Nancherla and Thomas Lennon, immediately take offense to this comment, and pause the episode for a moment just to sulk around their podiums. Luckily for Aparna and Tom, the proceeding video shows that very corgi going underneath a gate so it doesn't have to drop the branch — it's a Smart Dog! Aparna actually cheers!Andy: Hoisted by my own petard!
After Midnight	Early-Installment Weirdness	Taylor used to show a TikTok video at the beginning of the episode that would later appear in one of the episode's games. This only lasted the first five weeks of the show. In general, Taylor's intros were also much more brief, and her opening monologue, which is now a mainstay, wouldn't debut until four months in.
After Midnight	Enforced Plug	Played for laughs - one game is about doing an 8 second promo for the show itself, but tailored to specific cities across America.James Adomian: Hey Boston! Go f*ck yourself! After Midnight!
After Midnight	Every Episode Ending	For the first several months, For The Win — the @midnight tradition where the remaining two panelists give anonymous answers to a prompt, and the audience guesses which they like better. After some Retools, we transitioned into The Ultimate Challenge for the final two panelists, which is really just different kinds of guessing games.
After Midnight	Explain, Explain... Oh, Crap!	Taylor was very unhappy finding out that there is, in fact, an After Midnight subreddit.Taylor: This very program has inspired some wonder online. A few days ago, on the After Midnight subreddit [face immediately falls, mid-sentence] which I did not know existed and definitely won't go on later... Matt Rogers: Not good for your mental health. Taylor: No, not at all.
After Midnight	Extreme Close-Up	
After Midnight	Facepalm	The game Make Your Case on February 8, 2024, which concerns taking a real follow a panelist made on social media, and having to defend following that account. After Billy Eichner has been hazing Pete Holmes (because really, who doesn't?) for much of the show, Pete goes up to defend one of his own recent follows... and it's Billy's own account, prompting Billy's face to just collapse into his hands. Thankfully, Pete makes nice and has nothing but glowing words for Billy and his show.
After Midnight	Failed a Spot Check	The final game on October 2, 2024 involved showing a book called "A Light In The Park" on the screen, and asking panelists if it's a real book — they have to stand on either "Real" or "Fake" on the screen floor. Vinny Thomas has this lengthy screed about what he thinks the book is, and picks "Real." Michelle Collins points out that the font for "Fake" perfectly matches the font on the screen, prompting a massive Jaw Drop from Vinny as Michelle stands on "Fake." Of course, Michelle wins, and Vinny's clearly feeling about two inches tall as Michelle celebrates her victory.
After Midnight	Funny Background Event	When contestants are shown a video of a truck souped up with absurdly huge monster truck wheels, Guy Branum and Lisa Gilroy stare in awe, while Marcella Arguello is just throwing ass to the hip-hop song playing in the background.
After Midnight	The Gadfly	
After Midnight	Gallows Humor	October 23, 2024 saw the rare wheelchair user appear as a panelist, comedian Danielle Perez. Besides her podium being lowered to chair height to accommodate her, it passes without mention. Except for one, and it's a doozy — in a game where panelists have to tell all their secrets to a puppy they brought on stage, Taylor asks Danielle to tell the puppy how to make it in Hollywood.Danielle: [stage whisper] Get hit by a train!
After Midnight	Genki Girl	London Hughes, in both her appearances. She's so full of spirit and energy that when she was eliminated in her first episode, the audience practically revolted.
After Midnight	Grand Finale	Aired on Thursday, June 12, 2025, and had the winning panelists from that Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday — Gillian Jacobs, Marcella Arguello and Paul F. Tompkins — come back to compete to become "the winner of After Midnight." And in true After Midnight fashion, it's eventually decided by  an intentionally anticlimactic game of beyblades, which is won by perennial loser Marcella Arguello!
After Midnight	Group Hug	
After Midnight	Guest Host	Taylor was absent from the May 20, 2025 edition to go watch her brother's graduation. Who should step in to host the show? None other than recurring panelist and Dropout icon Lisa Gilroy, who would largely abide by Taylor's usual routine, except when giving out points, which she's unfathomably gratuitous about. By the end of the episode, Caitlin Reilly, Sandy Honig and Jared Goldstein all have over 200,000 points each. Jared points out after getting eliminated that he's "the highest scoring eliminated person of all time."
After Midnight	History Repeats	Two contestants to have competed while pregnant have won — Lauren Lapkus, and then three weeks later, Esther Povitsky. Mandy Moore of all people broke the streak.
After Midnight	Holiday Episode	A few changes to the game format when the show aired on a major holiday event:
After Midnight	Hollywood California	As announcer Laura Peek informs us at the top of each show, it's filmed at Paramount Studios in Hollywood.
After Midnight	Hyperspace Arsenal	Played for Laughs on March 14, 2024 when Reggie Conquest and Jordan Temple both have beanies on, and at some point during the Talk Show Portion, Paul F. Tompkins is suddenly seen wearing a beanie of his own, which he insists he's had on the entire time.
After Midnight	I Need a Freaking Drink	Since After Midnight is often populated by the left-wing, progressive types, there's a palpable bit of gloom hanging over the November 6, 2024 edition, after Kamala Harris lost the election to Donald Trump. Zach Noe Towers and Laura Peek do their best to keep good spirits, but Guy Branum goes the other way — halfway through the episode, when the panelists sit on the couch, Guy changes into pajamas and brings a real bottle of scotch on stage.
After Midnight	Implausible Deniability	Chris Fleming is eliminated on the March 26, 2024 edition, only for him to put a sign up in front of his podium that adds three extra 0s to his point total. So Taylor just decides to eliminate Matt Braunger instead, causing Chris to drop the facade immediately and face his elimination with dignity.
After Midnight	It's the Best Whatever, Ever!	The February 27th, 2024 episode with Caitlin Peluffo, Dulcé Sloan, and Jenny Zigrino had so much wild comedic energy between the three, that it was enough for Taylor to declare it her favorite episode ever before they even went into the first commercial break.
After Midnight	Lady in a Power Suit	Taylor's pantsuits became an instant trademark. She went on to have a variety of outfits as the show progressed into season 2, but her pantsuits remain her most iconic look. So iconic, in fact, that one Reddit user was ranking all her suits ("elite," "goated," "respect," "mid" and "nah") and that post got some airtime in the monologue on June 20, 2024... so Taylor could mercilessly dunk on them as an segue into explaining brainrot.
After Midnight	Large Ham	
After Midnight	Loophole Abuse	On the Super Bowl special, Wayne Brady, Maria Bamford and Kevin Smith had to flick paper footballs through a mock goalpost, getting points for every one that goes through. Maria struggles hard, until she suddenly stops, dumps her box of paper footballs out and just flings them through in bunches ("IT DOESN'T MATTER!!!"), because no one said she couldn't! And thus, she advances to FTW over Wayne Brady and ends the show with a Darkhorse Victory.
After Midnight	Loved by All	Any time Moo Deng (a baby pygmy hippo) comes up, expect everyone, including the studio audience, to react wildly and loudly.
After Midnight	Lucky Charms Title	Still has the @ symbol in the title, but it's more or less The Artifact, as it's still pronounced "after." Adam Pally spent an episode trying to work out the logistics of it (as in, the entire episode).
After Midnight	Meaningful Name	The show is on at 12:37am EST.
After Midnight	Moonwalk Dance	Arden Myrin does a knowingly terrible one on the January 30, 2024 edition, pulling her skirt down over her feet to cover how terrible it is.
After Midnight	Motor Mouth	Downplayed, as Pete Holmes isn't an especially fast talker so much as he's just incessant whenever he starts riffing off one of the game prompts, or off another contestant. Games become longer than normal just because Pete can't help himself. On the September 25, 2024 edition, they played a game where panelists have to fake being asleep one by one and other panelists have to try and stir them awake with jokes and jabs. Jess McKenna simply points out that this is the longest Pete has gone without talking, and Pete's out in five seconds.
After Midnight	My God, What Have I Done?	A comedic version, and twice over! When Kurt Braunohler is eliminated on the March 5th, 2024 edition, Taylor instructs him to call someone he cares about and tell them he lost. Kurt defaults to calling his wife, and in doing so, his wife puts his daughter on the phone. Kurt then has to tell his little girl that "the woman who runs this game made me lose," and she gets immediately upset, so an apologetic Kurt tries in vain to smooth it over and ends the call. An embarrassed Taylor immediately declares they are never doing that again, and she looks a little shaken up going into FTW.
After Midnight	My Parents Are Dead	Brendan Hunt on the February 26th, 2024 edition is asked during the Talk Show Portion what's missing from his life. He casually replies "living parents," breaking the audience's hearts. Thankfully, Marc Maron helpfully(?) chimes in next to him:Marc: I wanna just say that both my parents are still alive, and it's not great. Uh... Brendan: Thank you. Thank you. Marc: You got out, man; you got out. [Beat] I mean to say I'm sorry, for your loss. Brendan: Yeah- you did that in the wrong order. Marc: Yeah, I- I screwed up.
After Midnight	Namesake Gag	Ahead of Super Bowl LVIII, Taylor brings up "prop bets," which are bets not on the outcome of the game, but on strange things like "will Reba McEntire show cleavage while singing the national anthem." (That was really bet on, by the way.) Taylor asks what other prop bets they could make, and Pete Holmes gives us this gem:Pete: Will Usher live up to his namesake and show people to their seats?? [Taylor and the audience bust up laughing] Nico Santos: "These are my concessiooooons..." [audience is set off even more, and Taylor gives Nico an extra 100 points]
After Midnight	NO INDOOR VOICE	Eddie Pepitone's original appearance is a popular one, for his loud New York accent, combined with a penchant for the Rambling Old Man Monologue, swallowing multiple segments whole. Given that he was on with Jessica Kirson and Steph Tolev, two women that are hardly subtle themselves, this is no small feat. Half of the Group Chat is just Eddie shouting his lungs out and screwing up the segment, to the enjoyment of all involved.
After Midnight	"No. Just… No" Reaction	The first episode had a session about questionable cooking methods - one video was about what can only be described as the X-rated version of Saltbae, which got this reaction out of everyone.
After Midnight	Odd Friendship	Drag queen Monet X Change forms a bit of this with bro-comic Adam Ray, and they just riff off each other for homoerotic gags more and more as their episode goes on.
After Midnight	Off the Rails	As the show came into its own, panelists gradually got more comfortable bantering and this happened more and more.
After Midnight	Once an Episode	
After Midnight	The One That Got Away	Played for Laughs by none other than Jerry O'Connell. A game in his January 2024 episode invokes the TikTok meme of "we're girls, of course we ___" and panelists buzz in with variants on this formula. Jerry's becomes very gratuitous.Jerry: We knew each other from high school. Of course I'm gonna find your Instagram page late at night and not follow you but check to see if I'm hotter than your current husband; you had your shot, Amanda; you had your shot and you blew it!!! Taylor: Suck it, Amanda!
After Midnight	Overly Long Gag	
After Midnight	The Points Mean Nothing	Taken to the extent of Self-Deprecation whenever Taylor or a contestant points out that the show is "a fake game show."
After Midnight	Pop-Cultural Osmosis Failure	
After Midnight	Product Placement	Exaggerated on the May 23, 2024 episode, which is, for unexplained reasons, sponsored by Cuervo tequila. It finds its way into many games, the audience hoots and hollers at every mention of it, and everyone has a glass of the stuff during the Talk Show Portion. It's one of those things that gets more gratuitous until it becomes a bit in and of itself.
After Midnight	Proud to Be a Geek	
After Midnight	Pungeon Master	
After Midnight	Recurring Character	
After Midnight	Refuge in Audacity	This segment, where Taylor shows a TikToker named Samantha Hart, who explains that the formatting of her work email means that it shortens to... well, "shart." Taylor is quick to point out that they legally can't say that on TV, and in response, W. Kamau Bell, followed by Nish Kumar, starts chanting "SHART! SHART! SHART! SHART! SHART!" and getting the audience to join in, leaving Taylor in a fit of giggles.
After Midnight	Retool	
After Midnight	Rule of Three	Once during the Talk Show Portion, Taylor asked "what are three things that scare you?" to all three panelists, to everyone's amusement.
After Midnight	The Runner-Up Takes It All	As the person eliminated is given some kind of punishment — really just a prompt to make up some kind of losing speech or skit — it's been argued by viewers that the real winners are the ones who get a whole segment to themselves on the way out, and they're often more memorable than FTW. The episode with Esther Povitsky isn't memorable so much for her winning the episode, as it is for Kurt Braunohler's infamous phone call to his family to tell them he lost (which, to Taylor's horror, made his daughter upset for real). Maria Bamford once sacrificed some points to Laurie Kilmartin just so she could do an elimination... and go home early, of course. In the extreme case, Marcella Arguello used her elimination from her first appearance to start a bit that lasted through the end credits.
After Midnight	Running Gag	
After Midnight	Sarcasm Mode	Taylor asks Penn Jillette on the May 22, 2024 Talk Show Portion what it's like "being mightier than the sword." (Get it? Because his name is "Penn.") Penn Jillette responds by going full Sarcasm Mode for several minutes just to make fun of Taylor for such a lame joke.
After Midnight	Scenery Porn	The simple-looking yet dynamic set, with the big flip-phone main monitor, surrounded by translucent glass panels and lights that change vibrant colors depending on the situation.
After Midnight	Screw the Rules, I Make Them!	Downplayed, Taylor doesn't invoke this nearly as often as her predecessor did, save for one occasion where she said that in rehearsals, she found a game's rules complicated enough that she made the game worth 200 points instead of 100. She'll also award points in the Talk Show Portion if someone says something clever or interesting enough, even though it's not supposed to be a competitive segment.
After Midnight	Self-Deprecation	Taylor Tomlinson's stand-up jokes about her own struggles with mental health extend to this show, and contestants sometimes follow suit.
After Midnight	Sequel Series	To the original @Midnight, with frequent guests of the original showing up here, as well as some more recent faces in comedy, Taylor included.
After Midnight	Serious Business	May 20, 2024's edition features a game called Is It Caked? where panelists have to guess whether inanimate objects found online have a butt on them, aka Caked or Not Caked. Rory Scovel takes the game so seriously that it becomes sublimely ridiculous (in other words, extremely Rory Scovel).Rory: NONE OF YOU ARE ON THE CHOPPING BLOCK like I am! YOU DON'T KNOW HOW HARD this is! If I don't win, they're gonna kill my family! YOU HAVE IT EASY!!! [Taylor has to wipe her eyes from laughing]
After Midnight	Shirtless Scene	January 30, 2024's edition had a game called Better Life/Worse Life, where contestants are shown TikToks of some very eccentric influencers, and have to elaborate on why their lives are better or worse than them. The last one is a shirtless, muscle-bound guy in white jeans spraying perfume on himself. Jerry O'Connell chimed in proclaiming his life was better than this man's, by taking off his shirt and showing off his dad bod while dancing to the same stock music. Arden Myrin and Mary Lynn Rajskub get on the floor and do the worm around him just to be a part of... whatever this is, and thus everyone gets points. Jerry is made to take off his shirt again for a later segment.
After Midnight	Shout-Out	Six people saw a documentary about clowns that terrorise people... What I like about it is that you can light up a kids' room, or a sewer. And I saw it and I was like, this is it. (Beat) I said THIS IS IT!
After Midnight	Shout-Out to Shakespeare	April '24 - Jack Martin is eliminated, and his punishment is to give his idea of the "To be or not to be" speech from Hamlet. While holding Yorick's skull for some reason.
After Midnight	Sincerity Mode	Discussed in the final week of episodes, when Affion Crockett tries to be sincere in being thankful to get to be on the show, only for Marcella Arguello and Milana Vayntrub to instinctively joke about it, and Taylor can't help but laugh about how comedians are so bad at being sincere.
After Midnight	Sleepyhead	One challenge on the January 27, 2025 episode has the panelists help "stan" an adorable hamster. Unfortunately, it gets a little difficult since Taylor says that the hamster is frequently falling asleep throughout most of the challenge.
After Midnight	Sore Loser	Played for Laughs by a few eliminated contestants.
After Midnight	Special Guest	Occasionally someone who is not a panelist will show up just for a specific segment.
After Midnight	Speed Round	Hashtag Wars is still this, and sometimes there's another game of this nature in the elimination round.
After Midnight	Spelling Bee	Discussed when comedian Chloe Radcliffe dropped the word "fuselage" in one of her answers, and when Chris Fleming called her on using such a big word, Chloe claimed she won the 8th grade spelling bee. She demonstrates by spelling 'fuselage' to a big round of applause... even though, as Taylor points out, no one knows if she's right. (She was.) Moments later she then successfully spells "prosopometamorphopsia" ...by cheating and reading it off the big screen, with an irritated Taylor trying to cover the last few syllables.
After Midnight	Springtime for Hitler	Taylor's been up front on many occasions that the Talk Show Portion was intended as a Take That, Audience!note because at first many people thought she'd be hosting a talk show, and wouldn't get over it for the show's first few weeks, and the irony was not lost on Taylor when the segment gradually developed into a fan favorite. She embraced it, and it went from a one-minute goof-off with Seinfeldian Conversation to a fuller segment allowing the panelists to riff off each other a bit, and maybe even watch an extra video a panelist found on social media, just for fun. For Season 2, it's now used usually as a lead-in for Couch Game.
After Midnight	Squee	Taylor tries to go into the Talk Show Portion on July 18, 2024, but needs to take a moment to lose her mind over the fact that Mandy Moore is here! Mandy's a good sport and just lets Taylor gush for a minute about how Mandy's in so many of her comfort-watches.
After Midnight	The Stoner	
After Midnight	Stylistic Suck	
After Midnight	Take That, Audience!	Inspired by internet trolls who blasted the show initially for not being another late night talk show, Taylor started the Talk Show Portion, an interview segment with the three contestants that's usually as inane and arbitrary as possible. At the very least, it's just something else for comedians to riff off of, and at most it's an opportunity for a contestant to promote a current project.note Taylor once tried to promote her own comedy special during this segment, but cringed so much in doing so that she openly begged the contestants to plug their own projects so she doesn't "feel perceived." Taylor has even spelled out explicitly that she never had any interest in doing a talk show.Taylor: Well, that wraps up the Talk Show Portion; are you animals satisfied?!
After Midnight	Technologically Blind Elders	Averted by Caroline Rhea; when asked to identify what an NPC is for a game, she knows her daughter's video gaming habits so well that she gets it right off the bat (punctuated with a sassy hair flip for good measure). Not bad considering Caroline is pushing 60 by the time of this episode.
After Midnight	That Came Out Wrong	The first repeat guest, Kurt Braunohler, during the Talk Show Portion on March 5, 2024, is asked if anything's happened since last appearing, and he tells this unfortunate tale:Kurt: And then on the way home, I took an Uber, and I was getting out of the car, I just was like "Thank you so much," and I was leaving and he just instinctually went "Love you too." Taylor: Ohhhhh, that's amazing for you and terrible for him! Kurt: Yeah, and then I just closed the door and was like, "he didn't mean to do that." Taylor: Ohhh, five stars. Did you tip really big? Kurt: No, I gave him one star and said he's gross.
After Midnight	That Reminds Me of a Song	The Super Bowl special brings on internet sensation Marc Rebillet for "After Midnight's first ever halftime show" and it's an improvised EDM track about all the different things that happen in football, delivered in stream-of-consciousness as only Marc Rebillet can.
After Midnight	Trapped in TV Land	In the Halloween Episode: Marcella Arguello wins a haunted book. After opening it up, the lights go out and when they turn back on, Marcella is trapped in the giant flip-phone monitor, making her wonder if she's going viral.
After Midnight	Troll	
