AK Bingo	Rich in Dollars, Poor in Sense	In episode 402, the members discuss their monthly allowances.note That is, the cash they can spend each month, not necessarily their salary. In many Japanese households, paychecks from all working family members are pooled and the family treasurer, usually the mother, allocates the money for everybody's allowances and other needs. On average, the members receive 37,500 yen (about $350), but Kizaki Yuria gets 150,000 yen (around $1400) monthly, which is initially justified since she lives by herself and is expected to treat her juniors as a senior member. What shocks everyone is when she mentions offhand that she once spent almost 5000 yen for one breakfast, consisting of 2 asparagus and mushrooms. According to Nishino Miki, Yuria also cannot cook at all and only stocks food that can be immediately consumed by hand. Yuria: The Kizaki family has a motto: "Wear nice clothes and eat good food". Well, I spend a lot on food, I eat out almost every day...
AK Bingo	Ridiculously Photogenic	Inverted by Muto Orin, who complains in episode 508 that she always looks terrible on official merchandise and that it might have influenced her non-ranking in the elections. Muramoto, browsing the merch: This photo looks like a comedian crossdressing as a woman in London Hearts!
